  "description": "A warbler flew in to the oak that I was looking at. I quickly realized the warbler wasn't a Yellow-rumped Warbler. The bird was quite buffy underneath, whitish wing bars, and long tail. I also noticed a dark ear patch, with lighter eyeline and eye arches above and below each eye. The bill was thin and seemed long with the pink color on the lower mandible. A look at the back appeared to not have any streaking, and was greenish/gray. Look at photos.Behaviors: Stayed high in the oak tree.Call: nonePlumage: immature",
